, 
<figureCitation box="[243,287,1757,1782]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1781,1803]" captionTargetBox="[174,1411,618,1684]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,585,1719]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 25. Dorsal habitus. a. A. adaucta Cao &amp; Zhang sp. n.; b. A. akazu (Matsumura, 1932); c. A. badjawae Dworakowska, 1976; d. A. bauhinicola Dworakowska &amp; Viraktamath, 1978; e. A. curva Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; f. A. expansa Cao &amp; Zhang sp. n.; g. A. falcata Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; h. A. fusina Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; i. A. jinghongensis Cao &amp; Zhang sp. n.; j. A. liubanus Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; k. A. maculosa Dworakowska, 1977; l. A. parisakazu Cao &amp; Zhang sp. n.; m. A. plana Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; n. A. qinlingensis Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; o. A. quadrata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. n.; p. A. sphenoides Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; q. A. subapicifixa Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; r. A. subdentata Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; s. A. sufflata Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; t. A. symmetrica Cao &amp; Zhang sp. n.; u. A. triangulata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. n.; v. A. triprocessa Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; w. A. wolongensis Yang &amp; Zhang sp. n.; x. A. zelta Dworakowska, 1977." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444150/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">25h</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1822,2028]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">Body orange-brown. Face light yellowish, with anteclypeus and frontoclypeal area orange-brown. Eyes and basal triangles of mesonotum blackish. Fore wing brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1822,2028]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,383,1894,1919]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">Male genitalia:</emphasis>
Pygofer with single macroseta at cephalo-ventral angle of lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1156,1242,1894,1919]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[175,1418,210,1754]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 9. Anufrievia fusina Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage; c. apex of style; d. aedeagus, ventral view; e. aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444116/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">Fig. 9a</figureCitation>
), apex of dorsal appendage bifurcated, forcipiform, upper tooth nearly as long as lower one (
<figureCitation box="[1002,1086,1931,1956]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[175,1418,210,1754]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 9. Anufrievia fusina Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage; c. apex of style; d. aedeagus, ventral view; e. aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444116/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">Fig. 9b</figureCitation>
). Style with apical tooth longer than subapical tooth (
<figureCitation box="[403,488,1966,1991]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[175,1418,210,1754]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 9. Anufrievia fusina Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage; c. apex of style; d. aedeagus, ventral view; e. aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444116/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">Fig. 9c</figureCitation>
). Apical processes of aedeagal shaft quite short, hooked in lateral view; preatrial process extended to gonopore, apex in ventral view broad with serrated margin; gonopore near middle (
<figureCitation box="[1309,1422,2003,2028]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[175,1418,210,1754]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 9. Anufrievia fusina Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage; c. apex of style; d. aedeagus, ventral view; e. aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444116/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">Figs 9d, e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
